{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848467332,"sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","part":{"id":"prt_d78d12686001V8oFMOiwrgls3s","messageID":"msg_d78d11db1001LC3Ypfd5Ycxnca","sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ec9930db983349689063a146","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ## Atomic Tasks\n13: \n14: ### Phase 1: Proxy Configuration\n15: \n16: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ProxyConfig` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/config.go`\n17:   - Fields: `TargetURL` (string), `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleConns` (int), `IdleConnTimeout` (time.Duration), `ResponseHeaderTimeout` (time.Duration)\n18:   - Document each field with comments\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultProxyConfig()` function\n21:   - Returns default configuration with sensible timeouts\n22: \n23: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `RouteRule` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/route.go`\n24:   - Fields: `Path` (string), `Method` (string), `Target` (string), `StripPrefix` (bool), `Headers` (map[string]string)\n25:   - Methods: `Match()`, `Apply()`\n26: \n27: ### Phase 2: Proxy Core\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ReverseProxy` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/proxy.go`\n30:   - Fields: `config`, `transport`, `routes`, `metrics`, `logger`\n31: \n32: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewReverseProxy()` constructor\n33:   - Takes config and optional routes\n34:   - Returns initialized *ReverseProxy\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ServeHTTP()` method\n37:   - Matches incoming request to route\n38:   - Forwards request to target\n39:   - Streams response back to client\n40: \n41: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `proxyRequest()` method\n42:   - Copies request headers\n43:   - Handles body streaming\n44:   - Manages connection lifecycle\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `AddRoute()` and `RemoveRoute()` methods\n47:   - Thread-safe route management\n48: \n49: ### Phase 3: Health Checks\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `HealthChecker` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/health.go`\n52:   - Fields: `interval`, `timeout`, `unhealthyThreshold`, `targets` (map[string]*TargetHealth)\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `Start()` and `Stop()` methods\n55:   - Periodic health checking\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `checkTarget()` method\n58:   - HTTP GET to health endpoint\n59:   - Updates target health status\n60: \n61: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `GetHealthyTargets()` method\n62:   - Returns list of healthy targets for routing\n63: \n64: ### Phase 4: Connection Pooling\n65: \n66: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `ConnectionPool` in `pkg/router/proxy/pool.go`\n67:   - Manages reusable connections to targets\n68:   - Configurable max connections per target\n69: \n70: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `GetConnection()` and `ReleaseConnection()` methods\n71:   - Connection acquisition and release\n72: \n73: ### Phase 5: Metrics\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `ProxyMetrics` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/metrics.go`\n76:   - Fields: `requestsTotal` (Counter), `requestDuration` (Histogram), `activeConnections` (Gauge), `errorsTotal` (Counter), `upstreamHealth` (GaugeVec)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement metric recording methods\n79:   - `recordRequest()`, `recordError()`, `updateConnectionCount()`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestReverseProxy_ServeHTTP` in `pkg/router/proxy/proxy_test.go`\n84: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestReverseProxy_RouteMatching`\n85: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHealthChecker_CheckTarget`\n86: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestConnectionPool_GetConnection`\n87: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestProxyMetrics_RecordRequest`\n88: - [ ] **TEST-006**: Integration test with mock upstream server\n89: \n90: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n91: \n92: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/proxy/doc.go`\n93: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n94: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/router/README.md`\n95: \n96: ## Acceptance Criteria\n97: \n98: - [ ] Reverse proxy forwards requests to configured targets\n99: - [ ] Route matching works correctly\n100: - [ ] Health checks detect unhealthy targets\n101: - [ ] Connection pooling reduces connection overhead\n102: - [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n103: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n104: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n105: - [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented\n106: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n107: \n108: ## Dependencies\n109: \n110: - **Required**: None (core router functionality)\n111: - **Optional**: Prometheus client for metrics\n\n(End of file - total 111 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Proxy Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ProxyConfig` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/config.go`\n  - Fields: `TargetURL` (string), `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleConns` (int), `IdleConnTimeout` (time.Duration), `ResponseHeaderTimeout` (time.Duration)\n  - Document each field with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultProxyConfig()` function","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848467318,"end":1775848467329}}}}
