{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848472227,"sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","part":{"id":"prt_d78d139490012R31fJt9mxFoGS","messageID":"msg_d78d12bba001HKCbzKrgszByJ5","sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","type":"text","text":"Now I can see there's already a tasks.md file, but it focuses on a different architecture (proxy-based). Based on the design.md which shows the actual architecture with `router.go`, `handler.go`, `resolver.go`, `health.go`, `config.go`, and `types.go`, I need to update the tasks to match the documented design.","time":{"start":1775848472226,"end":1775848472226}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848507018,"sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","part":{"id":"prt_d78d13ea4001CdqKNzkCDpvI01","messageID":"msg_d78d12bba001HKCbzKrgszByJ5","sessionID":"ses_2872f3b74ffesXM8DRfJP6xLgp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_141a9577f53e4aaa9d0fee92","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Type Definitions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/types.go`\n  - Define `RouteEntry` struct with fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendURL`, `Health`, `UpdatedAt`\n  - Define `HealthStatus` struct with fields: `Healthy`, `LastCheck`, `Error`, `ConsecutiveFailures`, `mu`\n  - Define `ErrorResponse` struct for error responses\n  - Add `routeKey()` helper function\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/config.go`\n  - Define `RouterConfig` struct with all configuration fields\n  - Implement `DefaultRouterConfig()` function\n  - Implement config validation method\n\n### Phase 2: Router Core\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/router.go`\n  - Define `Router` struct with all required fields\n  - Implement `NewRouter()` constructor\n  - Implement `NewRouterWithClient()` constructor\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Router.Start()` method\n  - Start informer factory\n  - Wait for cache sync\n  - Start HTTP server\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Router.Shutdown()` method\n  - Stop accepting new connections\n  - Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n  - Shutdown informers\n  - Release resources\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Router.ServeHTTP()` method\n  - Delegate to handler\n\n### Phase 3: Route Resolver\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/resolver.go`\n  - Implement `Resolve()` method to lookup routes from sync.Map\n  - Implement `parsePath()` to extract namespace, resourceType, name from URL path\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement informer event handlers\n  - `onAgentRuntimeAdd()` - add route on CR creation\n  - `onAgentRuntimeUpdate()` - update route on CR update\n  - `onAgentRuntimeDelete()` - remove route on CR deletion\n  - `onCodeInterpreterAdd/Update/Delete()` - same for CodeInterpreter\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP Handler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/handler.go`\n  - Define `Handler` struct\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `Handler.ProxyRequest()` method\n  - Build backend URL from RouteEntry\n  - Clone request with new context\n  - Add forwarding headers (X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto)\n  - Execute request via httpClient.Do()\n  - Copy response headers and body\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Handler.writeErrorResponse()` method\n  - Write JSON error response with appropriate status code\n\n### Phase 5: Health Check Manager\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/health.go`\n  - Define `HealthChecker` struct\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `HealthChecker.Start()` method\n  - Periodic health check loop\n  - Check backend health at configured interval\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `HealthChecker.CheckHealth()` method\n  - HTTP GET to backend health endpoint\n  - Update HealthStatus based on response\n  - Apply health check failure policy (3 failures → mark unhealthy)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `HealthChecker.MarkUnhealthy()` and `HealthChecker.MarkHealthy()` methods\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `/healthz` HTTP handler\n  - Check informer sync status\n  - Return HTTP 200/503 based on health\n\n### Phase 6: Error Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Define error types in `pkg/router/errors.go`\n  - `ErrRouteNotFound`, `ErrNoHealthyBackends`, `ErrInvalidResourceType`, `ErrMalformedPath`\n  - `ErrBackendConnection`, `ErrBackendTimeout`, `ErrBackendUnavailable`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement error-to-HTTP-status mapping\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests (TDD)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/router/router_test.go`\n  - `TestRouter_Start`\n  - `TestRouter_Shutdown`\n  - `TestRouter_routeKey`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `pkg/router/resolver_test.go`\n  - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success`\n  - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound`\n  - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy`\n  - `TestResolver_ParsePath`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `pkg/router/health_test.go`\n  - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success`\n  - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure`\n  - `TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy`\n  - `TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `pkg/router/handler_test.go`\n  - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success`\n  - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError`\n  - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout`\n  - `TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders`\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `pkg/router/config_test.go`\n  - `TestDefaultRouterConfig`\n  - `TestRouterConfig_Validate`\n\n### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `pkg/router/router_integration_test.go`\n  - Test CRD creation triggers route addition\n  - Test CRD deletion triggers route removal\n  - End-to-end request routing\n  - Health check removes unhealthy backend\n  - Concurrent request handling\n\n### Phase 9: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/doc.go`\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Verify `pkg/router/design.md` is complete\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Router initializes with Kubernetes clientset and informers\n- [ ] HTTP requests are routed to correct backend based on CRD resources\n- [ ] Informer watches update routes on CRD create/update/delete\n- [ ] Namespace-based routing works correctly\n- [ ] `/healthz` endpoint returns accurate health status\n- [ ] Connection pooling configured with timeouts\n- [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown waits for in-flight requests\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with ≥85% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real CRDs\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | External | Resource types |\n| `net/http/httputil` | Go stdlib | Reverse proxy |\n| `go.uber.org/zap` | External | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | External | Metrics (optional) |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n                              ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-030 → TASK-031 → TASK-032\n                              ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → TASK-044\n                              ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-051\n                              ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-002 → TEST-003 → TEST-004 → TEST-005 → TEST-010\n                              ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-002 → DOC-003\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848506989,"end":1775848507014}}}}
